---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Bermuda Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/bermuda/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Bahamas for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahamas' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
  { title: 'UK for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/united-kingdom' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'bermudaFit', header: 'Bermuda Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BMD$550-785/mo', bermudaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BMD$645-920/mo', bermudaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BMD$495-705/mo', bermudaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BMD$460-655/mo', bermudaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local HIP/FutureCare', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: 'BMD$400-700/mo', bermudaFit: 'Required' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BMD$495-785', annual: 'BMD$5,940-9,420' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BMD$680-1,045', annual: 'BMD$8,160-12,540' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BMD$915-1,405', annual: 'BMD$10,980-16,860' },
  { category: 'Bermuda HIP (Mandatory)', monthly: 'BMD$400-700/mo', annual: 'BMD$4,800-8,400' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'BMD$1,500-3,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bermuda 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Bermuda. British territory, pink beaches, proximity to US East Coast, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Bermuda"
  subheadline="Bermuda offers British sophistication, pink sand beaches, US proximity, and high quality of life—an exclusive island destination for retirement with mandatory health insurance requirements."
  heroImage="/images/countries/bermuda-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Bermuda</h2>
  <p>
    Bermuda offers British heritage, beautiful pink beaches, safe environment, and 2-hour flight to US East Coast. For those seeking exclusive island retirement with first-world standards, Bermuda delivers though at one of the world highest costs of living.
  </p>

  <p>
    Hamilton is the capital with shops and restaurants. Southampton and Warwick have resort areas. Somerset and Sandys offer quieter living. The entire island is only 21 square miles—everywhere is accessible. Golf, sailing, and social clubs are central to expatriate life.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good local; US evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BMD$8,000-15,000/month (~same USD); extremely high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subtropical; mild year-round; minimal hurricanes</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> British; exclusive; safe</li>
      <li><strong>Insurance:</strong> Mandatory HIP coverage for residents</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Bermuda Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Bermuda has good healthcare for its size—King Edward VII Memorial Hospital is the main facility. Most routine care handled locally. Complex procedures typically require evacuation to Boston or New York (2-hour flight). Medical specialists visit regularly from US hospitals.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare is expensive—Bermuda health costs among world highest. Mandatory insurance (HIP) covers basic care. Most residents supplement with additional coverage. Boston hospitals (Mass General, Brigham) serve as regional specialists.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Mandatory Insurance</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Bermuda requires health insurance for all residents—HIP (Health Insurance Plan) is mandatory minimum. FutureCare covers seniors 65+. Most residents add supplemental coverage for US treatment. International insurance can supplement but doesn't replace HIP requirement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Bermuda has limited retirement options:
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Resident Certificate (PRC)</h3>
  <p>
    For those with Bermuda connections or long-term residence. Competitive; controlled by government policy. Most difficult path.
  </p>

  <h3>Residential Certificate</h3>
  <p>
    For those purchasing property over BMD$2.5 million+. Allows residence but not work. Main option for wealthy retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Work Permit Transition</h3>
  <p>
    Those with long work permit history may qualify for residential status upon retirement. Check specific eligibility.
  </p>

  <h3>UK/British Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    British Overseas Territory—some advantages but still requires permission for residence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Bermuda:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>HIP:</strong> Mandatory health insurance for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>FutureCare:</strong> Senior-specific coverage (65+)</li>
    <li><strong>Supplemental:</strong> Strongly recommended for US coverage</li>
    <li><strong>US evacuation:</strong> Essential for complex conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Bermuda</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Mandatory HIP/FutureCare provides local base coverage. International insurance supplements with US coverage for complex care. Boston/New York hospitals are your specialists. Budget for both mandatory local and supplemental international coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Bermuda, mandatory + supplemental coverage needed:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Bermuda</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>HIP/FutureCare:</strong> Mandatory; non-negotiable local coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Supplements with US network access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Boston network:</strong> Key specialist referral destination</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare supplemental coverage for US access from Bermuda.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in Bermuda include mandatory + supplemental:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>HIP compliance:</strong> Meet mandatory minimum; add supplements strategically</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Reduce supplemental premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Network plans:</strong> Use designated US hospitals for better rates</li>
    <li><strong>Annual review:</strong> Bermuda insurers offer various packages</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Executive Retiring, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $10,000/month pension. Residential certificate via property. Southampton.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> FutureCare mandatory + Cigna Global for US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BMD$1,100/month total. Boston specialists; island living.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Finance Professional, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £7,000/month income. Long-term PRC holder. Hamilton area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> FutureCare + BUPA Global with UK backup.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BMD$1,300/month total. UK and US healthcare options.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Insurance Executive, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> C$8,000/month pension. Residential certificate. Warwick.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> FutureCare + Allianz Care international.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BMD$1,000/month total. Industry connections; global coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Bermuda really that expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—one of world most expensive places to live. Housing, food, utilities all premium. Budget BMD$8,000-15,000/month minimum for comfortable living. Those on fixed income should calculate carefully before committing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can anyone retire to Bermuda?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        No—residence is restricted. Main path is purchasing property over BMD$2.5 million (ARV threshold). Some with long work permit history may qualify. Permanent residence is controlled. This is not a destination for average retirees.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How close is US healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        2-hour flight to Boston or New York—multiple daily flights. Air ambulance available 24/7. Many Bermuda residents have established relationships with Boston hospitals. US East Coast proximity is major healthcare advantage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about hurricanes?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Bermuda is north of main hurricane belt—storms occur but less frequently than Caribbean. Building codes are strict; most structures withstand storms well. Not immune to hurricanes but lower risk than southern islands.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes for supplemental coverage in Bermuda.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Bermuda authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
